<!-- filters (optional)

if you have a lot of filters, a scrollbar will appear.

do not remove the first filter, but add or remove as many of the ones below as you want. a filter or "tag" works like so:

<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".tag">tag name</a></li>

ONLY change .tag and >tag name<. i recommend keeping the tags short but something you'll remember. see some examples below:

<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".female">female</a></li>
<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".leo">star sign:leo</a></li>
<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".narnia">universe: narnia</a></li>

if you want something to be classed by two things (e.g. favourite females), you'll put together the tags .fav and .female like so:

<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".fav.female">favourite females</a></li>

if you want to make sections of tags/filters, pop a <hr> in between each.

-->
        
<div id="sort">
<ul id="filters" class="option-set clearfix" data-option-key="filter">

    <h3>filter by:</h3>
<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".charac" class="selected">all</a></li>
<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".fav" class="fav">favourites</a></li>
<hr>
<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".female">female</a></li>
<li><a href="#filter" data-option-filter=".male">male</a></li> 
</ul>
    </div>
        
</div>
    

    
</div>    



<ul id="con" class="characters">

<!-- 

a note on tagging/filtering.

<li class="charac...."> is where you put the tags. LEAVE 'charac' there. don't touch it. 

remove 'put your tags here' from the line and add whatever ones you want, making sure they match with what you put above. e.g.:

<li class="charac female leo narnia"> 
is a female character who is a leo and set in the 'narnia' universe.

<li class="charac male fav virgo"> 
is a favourite male character who is a virgo. 

it doesn't matter what order you put things in. if you want it to come up with the little red heart and be included in favourites, make sure you put 'fav' in there somewhere. 

-->




